TITLE: Making API Requests with OAuth Token in Ktor
DESCRIPTION: Function for making authenticated requests to Google API using the OAuth token stored in the session. Demonstrates how to use the token in the Authorization header.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ktorio/ktor-documentation/blob/main/topics/server-oauth.md#2025-04-09_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
suspend fun getPersonalGreeting(client: HttpClient, token: String): String {
    val response = client.get("https://www.googleapis.com/oauth2/v3/userinfo") {
        headers {
            append(HttpHeaders.Authorization, "Bearer $token")
        }
    }
    return response.bodyAsText()
}
```

