TITLE: Creating a Data Transformation Benchmark Plugin in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: This plugin demonstrates how to use call attributes to measure and log the time taken between receiving a request and reading its body. It stores the timestamp when the request is received and calculates the delay when the body is read.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ktorio/ktor-documentation/blob/main/topics/server-custom-plugins.md#2025-04-09_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
val DataTransformationBenchmarkPlugin = createApplicationPlugin(name = "DataTransformationBenchmarkPlugin") {
    // This plugin will intercept all calls and measure the time to obtain the request body
    onCall { call ->
        // Store the timestamp when the request is received
        call.attributes.put(StartTimeKey, System.currentTimeMillis())
    }

    onCallReceive { call ->
        // Calculate and log the delay when the request body is read
        val delay = System.currentTimeMillis() - call.attributes[StartTimeKey]
        call.application.log.info("Read body delay (ms): $delay")
    }
}

private val StartTimeKey = AttributeKey<Long>("StartTimeKey")
```

