TITLE: Configuring HttpSend Plugin for Request Retries in Ktor
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to configure the HttpSend plugin to intercept HTTP requests and implement retry logic. The example shows how to monitor response status codes and retry requests when server returns error responses (4xx or 5xx status codes).
SOURCE: https://github.com/ktorio/ktor-documentation/blob/main/topics/client-http-send.md#2025-04-09_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
val client = HttpClient(CIO) {
    plugin(HttpSend) {
        maxSendCount = 2
        intercept { request, pipeline ->
            val response = pipeline.execute(request)
            when (response.status.value) {
                in 400..499 -> throw PrintError(response)
                else -> response
            }
        }
    }
}
```

