TITLE: Creating SslSettings Class for SSL Configuration in Kotlin
DESCRIPTION: This snippet creates an SslSettings class that loads a certificate from an existing KeyStore file and provides functions for obtaining different SSL configurations like SSLContext, TrustManager, and SSLSocketFactory.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ktorio/ktor-documentation/blob/main/topics/client-ssl.md#2025-04-09_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
class SslSettings(private val keyStoreFile: String, private val keyStorePassword: String) {
    // Load the KeyStore with the self-signed certificate
    private val keyStore = KeyStore.getInstance(KeyStore.getDefaultType()).apply {
        val file = File(keyStoreFile)
        file.inputStream().use { fileInput ->
            load(fileInput, keyStorePassword.toCharArray())
        }
    }

    // TrustManager configured to trust the self-signed certificate
    val trustManager: X509TrustManager = TrustManagerFactory.getInstance(TrustManagerFactory.getDefaultAlgorithm()).apply {
        init(keyStore)
    }.trustManagers.first() as X509TrustManager

    // SSLContext configured to use the custom TrustManager
    val sslContext = SSLContext.getInstance("TLS").apply {
        init(null, arrayOf(trustManager), SecureRandom())
    }

    // SSLSocketFactory configured with the SSLContext
    val sslSocketFactory: SSLSocketFactory = sslContext.socketFactory

    fun sslContextFactory() = SslContextFactory.Client().apply {
        sslContext = this@SslSettings.sslContext
    }
}
```

