TITLE: Handling Multipart Form Data Upload
DESCRIPTION: Comprehensive example of handling multipart form data including file uploads and form fields with size limits.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ktorio/ktor-documentation/blob/main/topics/server-requests.md#2025-04-09_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
post("/upload") {
    val multipart = call.receiveMultipart(formFieldLimit = 100L * 1024L * 1024L)
    multipart.forEachPart { part ->
        when (part) {
            is PartData.FormItem -> {
                val name = part.name
                val value = part.value
                // Handle form field
            }
            is PartData.FileItem -> {
                val name = part.name
                val originalFileName = part.originalFileName
                part.provider().use { input ->
                    File("uploads/$originalFileName").writeBytes(input.readBytes())
                }
            }
            else -> {}
        }
        part.dispose()
    }
    call.respondText("Upload successful")
}
```

