TITLE: Implementing LocalDate Converter in DataConversion Plugin
DESCRIPTION: Complete example showing how to define a custom converter for LocalDate type with encoding and decoding functions for date format conversion.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ktorio/ktor-documentation/blob/main/topics/server-data-conversion.md#2025-04-09_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
install(DataConversion) {
    convert<LocalDate> {
        // DateTimeFormatter is used to declare the date format
        val format = DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern("yyyy-MM-dd")

        // deserialization: string -> LocalDate
        decode { values ->
            values.singleOrNull()?.let { LocalDate.parse(it, format) }
        }

        // serialization: LocalDate -> string
        encode { value ->
            when (value) {
                null -> listOf()
                is LocalDate -> listOf(value.format(format))
                else -> throw DataConversionException("Cannot convert $value as LocalDate")
            }
        }
    }
}
```

