TITLE: Configuring Caching for Static Files in Ktor
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to configure the Cache-Control header for HTTP caching of static files in Ktor using the cacheControl() function. It sets different caching policies based on file extensions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ktorio/ktor-documentation/blob/main/topics/server-static-content.md#2025-04-09_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: kotlin
CODE:
```
install(CachingHeaders) {
    options { _, outgoingContent ->
        when (outgoingContent.contentType?.withoutParameters()) {
            ContentType.Text.CSS -> CachingOptions(CacheControl.MaxAge(maxAgeSeconds = 24 * 60 * 60))
            ContentType.Application.JavaScript -> CachingOptions(CacheControl.MaxAge(maxAgeSeconds = 24 * 60 * 60))
            else -> null
        }
    }
}
routing {
    staticFiles("/", File("files")) {
        cacheControl {
            when {
                url.encodedPath.endsWith(".css") -> listOf(CacheControl.MaxAge(maxAgeSeconds = 24 * 60 * 60))
                url.encodedPath.endsWith(".js") -> listOf(CacheControl.MaxAge(maxAgeSeconds = 24 * 60 * 60))
                else -> emptyList()
            }
        }
    }
}
```

